Introduction


The main aim is predicting breast cancer patients chance of survival.

We have follow these steps:

  • Clean the data
  • Augment the data
  • Create some plots
  • Statistical analysis
  • Create the prediction tool
  • Create the presentation

Materials and methods

Materials


We are working with a dataset about Breast Cancer that we have obtained from kaggle website

This is the dataset we are working with:

Cleaning the data


## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'

Cleaning the data


Changes
Column names
Variable names contained special invisible chars ( ) which were removed
Birth_control was renamed to not contain parenthesis in variable name
Variable values
Missing values were encoded to NA_real (numeric NA)
For binary variables, if another char than 0 or 1 is found, this is assumed to be a typing error and is set = 1 (greedy approach)
Blood type had one value of 44 (mistake) which was changed to NA
Birth dates of other than 4 numbers were set to NA
Filter out samples
Only look at women as they are the risk group of breast cancer (few men are hit)
Only look at women > 20 years, as we wish to mainly focus on the risk group (age =risk) (0 cases in UK for women < 20 over 3 years)
Filter out samples that are believed to have errors in weight
Filter out a single woman who is set to not yet have her period, but have experience in pregnancy (does not make sense = error)
Removing columns
Remove singular columns (with only one value for all samples)

Augmenting the data


Changes
Values changed
Categorical variables or more than 2 categories where encoded by their name instead of numbers
Binary categories were kept
All categorical values were changed to type; factor
Numeric values were kept
Adding columns
Columns explaining factor variables, like education, mestrual_age, menopausal_age‚Ä¶
Age at treatment were calculated from birthdate year treatment year
